From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Schiffhauer <alexander.schiffhauer@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 10:48:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] win32u: Avoid cross-process deadlock in load_desktop_driver.

load_desktop_driver() sends WM_NULL to the desktop window with
the comment "wait for graphics driver to be ready", using
send_message() - which is send_message_timeout(..., timeout=0),
i.e. an unbounded wait.

Two failure modes:

 1. When the caller IS the desktop owner thread (the wine-wayland
    explorer.exe /desktop main thread runs load_display_driver
    itself), wine routes the SendMessage as an inter-thread
    message and parks the thread waiting for a reply that would
    have to come from itself.

 2. When two wine processes both reach load_desktop_driver near-
    simultaneously (e.g. Battle.net.exe spawns while explorer.exe
    is finishing driver load), each thread sends WM_NULL to a
    desktop hwnd owned by the OTHER thread, and both park
    forever in send_inter_thread_message ->
    wait_message_reply -> NtWaitForMultipleObjects.

Backtrace from a stuck process:
  send_message -> send_message_timeout -> process_message
                -> send_inter_thread_message
                -> wait_message_reply -> NtWaitForMultipleObjects

Skip the send entirely when the caller already owns the desktop
window's thread; otherwise bound the wait with SMTO_ABORTIFHUNG
and a 5-second timeout so a peer in the same state can't wedge
us indefinitely.  The send is purely a sync barrier - timing
out and proceeding with NtUserGetProp returns at worst a stale
guid, matching behaviour before the barrier was added.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Schiffhauer <alexander.schiffhauer@gmail.com>
---
 dlls/win32u/driver.c                     |    9 ++++++---
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/win32u/driver.c b/dlls/win32u/driver.c
index 11111111..22222222 100644
--- a/dlls/win32u/driver.c
+++ b/dlls/win32u/driver.c
@@ -961,7 +961,11 @@ static BOOL load_desktop_driver( HWND hwnd )
     user_check_not_lock();

     asciiz_to_unicode( driver_load_error, "The explorer process failed to start." );  /* default error */
-    /* wait for graphics driver to be ready */
-    send_message( hwnd, WM_NULL, 0, 0 );
+    /* wait for graphics driver to be ready: bounded send so a peer in the same
+     * load_desktop_driver() path can't wedge us, and skipped entirely when we
+     * already own the desktop hwnd (the wait reply would have to come from us). */
+    if (get_window_thread( hwnd, NULL ) != GetCurrentThreadId())
+        send_message_timeout( hwnd, WM_NULL, 0, 0,
+                              SMTO_ABORTIFHUNG | SMTO_NORMAL, 5000, FALSE );

     guid_atom = HandleToULong( NtUserGetProp( hwnd, prop_nameW ));
